This paper is about improving neural machine translation (NMT) systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The proposed model involves using an inter-sentence gate to control the flow of information between adjacent sentences, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves encoding and decoding sentences, which are tasks commonly associated with neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on translation tasks, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV) and NLP.
